description:
&lt;p&gt;The Oxton Unit is a 12 bedded heart failure ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a part time receptionist to join our friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for providing a friendly and efficient service to patients, visitors and professional bodies. Applicants must be confident communicators with the ability to liaise with staff at all levels. They will be responsible for ensuring medical notes for patients are ready for elective admissions and follow up appointments booked in on discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential qualities include strong organisational and time management skills with the ability to multi-task and work under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should have demonstrable experience of working in a patient orientated environment. Applicants should be experienced in using I.T. systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full training will be given to the right candidate on all hospital based systems along with a structured induction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is for 21.5 hours Mon- Fri, you will be required to work on a Wednesday day other hours and times negotiable. Please contact before applying to ensure that it is suitable for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAmy KnowlesJob titleWard sisterEmail addressamy.knowles@nuh.nhs.ukTelephone number72232&lt;/p&gt;
